article.headline: (24) BOSTON COLLEGE 90, HOLY CROSS 43
article.story:
CHESTNUT HILL, Massachusetts (Ticker) -- Jessalyn Deveny 
scored 21 points and Amber Jacobs added 20 as No. 24 Boston
College cruised to a 90-43 victory over Holy Cross.

Deveny, who was named BIG EAST Co-Player of the Week on Monday,
converted 10-of-12 free-throw attempts and pulled down five
rebounds.

Jacobs went 7-of-8 from the field, including 3-of-4 from behind
the 3-point arc, and handed out six assists.

Clare Droesch chipped in with eight points, seven rebounds and
four assists for the Eagles (5-0), who recorded 31 points off of
24 turnovers by the Crusaders.

Sarah Placek connected on a pair of 3-point baskets en route to
netting 14 points for Holy Cross (3-3), which has dropped its
past two games by a total of 81 points.
